The paper deals with statistical distance measures and their embeddings into low dimensional spaces, which are topics that are commonly studied in information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the use of these distance measures in computer vision (cs.CV) and the embeddability of these measures into metric spaces, which is a topic that falls under the scope of computer science and information science (cs.SI).
